extracted_text: No structure shall have a vertical height in excess of 35 feet as measured from the highest point of the original natural grade of the land on which the building sits (i.e. the land directly beneath the footprint of the building) to the highest point of the structure.
llm_output.rationale: The section on maximum building height (§ 154.140) provides a general 35 foot height limit for all structures, but does not specify any different limit for CS-1 zoning. Without more specific information about CS-1 regulations, this appears to be the applicable height limit.
